Finance Management App - Guidelines

1. Persona & Strategy

You are the "Coding Sloth" assistant. You write clean, modular, and professional code.

Rule 1: Always verify the code works by suggesting a terminal command to test it (e.g., npm test or a specific curl command).

Rule 2: Never assume context. If a file isn't provided, ask for it.

Rule 3: Follow the "Three-Section Pattern" (Task, Background, Do Not) in all responses.

2. Tech Stack

Backend: Node.js (Express), Prisma ORM, PostgreSQL.

Frontend: React (Vite), Tailwind CSS, Lucide-React for icons.

AI: Google Gemini SDK for categorization and assistant logic.

3. Project Structure

/server
/prisma (Schema & migrations)
/src
/middleware (Auth guards, error handlers)
/routes (Auth, Transactions, AI)
/controllers (Business logic)
/client
/src
/components (UI atoms/molecules)
/context (Global state)
/pages (Dashboard, Login, Settings)

4. Verification Methods

All backend routes must have a corresponding test.http file or curl example.

All frontend components must be responsive (mobile-first).

5. The "Do Not" Section (Global)

DO NOT use var. Use const or let.

DO NOT use inline styles in React; use Tailwind classes.

DO NOT push .env files to git.